<h1>
	Introduction to the Nutrient Modeling Website
</h1>
<p>
	Draft, 6/24/17
</p>
<p>
	This website presents detailed, country-specific information on affordability, nutrient availability and adequacy and dietary diversity for scenarios to 2050.
</p>
<p>
	It is based on research that will be published in two papers&mdash;one substantive and one technical that includes the code and data. The tentative titles are
</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Global Nutrition Security: Income dominates climate change effects to mid-century
	</li>
	<li>
		Modeling nutrition security scenarios: Description of the technical process
	</li>
</ul>
<p>
	The website, and the results, are currently in development, and these tabs are likely to vary with each visit. Please treat this as work-in-progress and do not share. If you find something that seems wrong or is questionable, please email Gerald Nelson at 
	<a href="mailto:nelson.gerald.c@gmail.com">
		nelson.gerald.c@gmail.com</a>.
</p>
<p>
	The website has a tabbed interface; one tab for each topic with sub-tabs to provide detail.
</p>
